#Basic settings to render 2D technical illustrations with Freestyle renderer

##With Blender Render

1. Select 'Blender Render'  
   ![Blender_Render](../img/09.png)

2. Render tab -> Select 'Freestyle'

3. Set 'Line thickness'  
   ![Render_tab](../img/10.png)

4. Render Layers tab -> De-select all 'Passes', then only the lines (strokes) are rendered.  
   ![Render_Layers](../img/11.png)

5. Freestyle Line Style -> Select 'Geometry'  
   ![Render_Layers](../img/12.png)

##With Cycles Renderer

1. Select 'Cycles'  
   ![Blender_Render](../img/13.png)

2. Render tab -> Select 'Freestyle'

3. Set 'Line thickness'  
   ![Render_tab](../img/14.png)

5. Freestyle Line Style -> Select 'Geometry'

4. Render Layers tab -> De-select 'Use Surfaces'

4. Render Layers tab -> De-select all 'Passes', then only the lines (strokes) are rendered.  
   ![Render_Layers](../img/15.png)
